a tulip guy to you?

00:39.331 --> 00:40.946
(laughs) Luke?

00:40.999 --> 00:42.034
(sighs)

00:42.125 --> 00:46.334
What do you want? Anything.
What is gonna make you happy?

00:46.380 --> 00:47.586
I want to go back to work,

00:47.631 --> 00:50.589
I want to have not been shot
by my own gun,

00:50.634 --> 00:55.503
and I want to walk down the hallway
without using my fiancee as a walker.

00:58.725 --> 01:00.932
You do make
a real sexy walker, though.

01:00.978 --> 01:02.684
Uaughs)

01:02.729 --> 01:05.345
Okay. I'll tell you what.
Let's go to the cafeteria,

01:05.399 --> 01:06.764
and I'll get us a Scrabble board.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.274
— Oh, honey, you're terrible at Scrabble.
— Oh, yeah?

01:09.319 --> 01:11.856
— Yeah. Yeah.
— (laughs)

01:11.905 --> 01:14.112
Race ya.

01:14.700 --> 01:18.659
(police radio chatter)

01:20.414 --> 01:23.372
(Dov) I thought kids didn't exercise
these days!

01:23.417 --> 01:25.203
Man down! Hold still.

01:25.252 --> 01:27.413
Ah! You're hurting my head!

01:27.462 --> 01:30.795
That's so you don't bang it, accuse me
of police brutality, you little creep.

01:30.841 --> 01:32.331
Hey! Stop!

01:32.384 --> 01:35.251
All right. All right,
put the pillowcase down.

01:35.304 --> 01:37.260
Get down on the ground,
hands on your head.

01:38.599 --> 01:39.429
(grunts)

01:40.976 --> 01:42.762
Dov!

01:42.811 --> 01:43.971
Got him.

01:44.021 --> 01:44.976
(dog whimpers)

01:45.022 --> 01:46.478
Yeah, he got him.

01:46.523 --> 01:48.024
Down now.

01:48.066 --> 01:50.273
(Chris) Yeah, he's got him.

01:50.319 --> 01:51.775
This is Epstein...

01:51.820 --> 01:54.562
Yes, he does. Hmm?

01:54.615 --> 01:57.448
(blender whirring)

01:59.995 --> 02:01.826
All hail the conquering heroes.

02:01.872 --> 02:03.203
Oh. Can I not?

02:03.248 --> 02:04.533
— Hey.
— Hey, baby.

02:04.583 --> 02:06.665
Broke up a dogfighting ring
in Little Portugal.

02:06.710 --> 02:08.325
Bunch of guys stealing house pets,

02:08.378 --> 02:10.790
using them as bait,
giving them a taste of blood.

02:10.839 --> 02:12.375
You——You personally broke it up?

02:12.424 --> 02:16.758
Well... we were there.
We were near.

02:16.803 --> 02:20.091
(dog whining)

02:20.140 --> 02:21.596
No.

02:21.642 --> 02:23.178
Just——No, just——

02:23.226 --> 02:24.477
No.

02:24.519 --> 02:26.896
Chris, we can't keep that.

02:26.938 --> 02:28.439
No, yeah, look——
look, we just——

02:28.482 --> 02:30.939
We're just gonna keep him
till we find his parents, okay?

02:30.984 --> 02:33.225
We're like his, uh...
we're like his foster parents.

02:33.278 --> 02:34.654
We're already Dov's foster parents.

02:34.696 --> 02:36.311
Bite me, Casper.

02:36.365 --> 02:39.653
You know what, Chris? You decide
who you want licking your feet tonight.

02:39.701 --> 02:40.941
— How about that?
— (Dov) Ooh.

02:40.994 --> 02:43.030
It's like "Sophie's Choice"...

02:43.080 --> 02:44.195
only different.

02:45.749 --> 02:47.910
I love this little fellow already.

02:47.959 --> 02:49.335
— Hey.
- (dog yirJS)

02:49.378 --> 02:51.369
Oh, uh... (clears throat)
We'll talk later.

02:51.421 --> 02:52.797
(whispers) Yeah.
(dog whimpers)

02:52.839 --> 02:56.081
Don't worry, little buddy.
Her bark's worse than her bite.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.123
(door closes)

02:57.177 --> 02:59.463
You know, sometimes...
I don't get that guy.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.469
One of life's great mysteries.
(beep)

03:01.515 --> 03:03.551
Time for a little "Deathdomain"?

03:03.600 --> 03:05.682
Want to play till he gets back?
(video game auto racing sounds)

03:05.727 --> 03:09.345
— Are you ready to be humiliated?
— Oh, game on.

03:09.398 --> 03:10.729
(whispers) Bastard.

03:12.818 --> 03:14.854
(police radio chatter)

03:17.489 --> 03:18.945
Bye,you.

03:18.990 --> 03:20.446
Bye, Mommy.

03:20.492 --> 03:21.982
(giggles) Mwah.

03:23.995 --> 03:26.532
You gonna be working
late again tonight?

03:26.581 --> 03:28.742
I'll try and be home by dinner.
I know you got hockey.

03:28.792 --> 03:32.410
Oh, don't worry. I already told 'em
that I couldn't make it.

03:32.462 --> 03:34.999
It's fine.
Just get home when you can.

03:35.048 --> 03:37.334
I'm serious, it's cool.

03:37.384 --> 03:39.295
— Thank you.
— I can do it.

03:39.344 --> 03:40.800
Okay.

03:40.846 --> 03:42.302
Bye. Thank you.

03:42.347 --> 03:44.008
Hi.

03:44.057 --> 03:46.594
Hi. I didn't know
you've been working late.

03:47.060 --> 03:48.345
Yeah, I have, a few times.

03:48.395 --> 03:51.887
Oh. 'cause I've been
working late every night

03:51.940 --> 03:53.805
for the past two weeks,
and I don't remember seeing you.

03:54.151 --> 03:56.358
You've been working late
every night the past two weeks?

03:56.403 --> 03:58.314
Don't change the subject.

03:58.363 --> 04:00.524
(man) All right, all right.
See you tomorrow.

04:00.574 --> 04:01.939
I don't know what to do about Luke.

04:01.992 --> 04:04.449
I mean, I've tried everything——
action movies,

04:04.494 --> 04:07.827
crosswords, Sudoku.
I've even offered to play poker.

04:07.873 --> 04:11.206
What is gonna cheer him up?
Don't say porn.

04:11.334 --> 04:13.916
I would have thought the poker.
Maybe a little porn.

04:13.962 --> 04:14.997
Shut up.

04:15.046 --> 04:17.253
Guy's all hopped up on painkillers.
Give him a break.

04:17.299 --> 04:18.379
I know. I mean,

04:18.425 --> 04:20.507
I know the doctor said that he
could be down after the surgery,

04:20.552 --> 04:23.635
but I am doing everything wrong.
I'm saying all the wrong things.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.012
— Well, give him some space.
— I don't like space,

04:26.057 --> 04:28.309
because space doesn't
involve me doing something.

04:28.351 --> 04:30.137
You know, it's kind of like time.

04:30.187 --> 04:31.051
Time doesn't work for me either.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.561
Time and space——
two things that don't work for you.

04:33.607 --> 04:34.938
Pretty much.

04:34.983 --> 04:36.314
(door release buzzes)
Hey.

04:36.359 --> 04:38.315
Dale from next door is taking
the dog out this afternoon.

04:38.361 --> 04:40.192
You better watch yourself
with the dog, man.

04:40.238 --> 04:42.980
— You heard what Gail said.
— Aw, she's just being mean.

04:43.033 --> 04:45.445
You don't dump the pooch,
Shorty might dump you.

04:45.494 --> 04:47.200
So what? You hate having
Gail around anyways.

04:47.245 --> 04:49.236
You're right.
I do hate having Gail around.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.995
So what do you care
if she dumps me?

04:51.041 --> 04:52.030
— Tell him.
— Well——

04:52.793 --> 04:53.873
Because”.

04:55.003 --> 04:56.163
Gail's awesome.

04:56.213 --> 04:57.794
Little side bet last night,

04:57.839 --> 04:59.340
right before I crushed
your friend here.

05:00.342 --> 05:01.832
— It was a total fluke.
— (laughs) Yeah, right.

05:01.885 --> 05:03.841
— I had a bad game.
— What?

05:03.887 --> 05:04.717
I had a bad game.

05:04.763 --> 05:08.301
So Epstein's got to spend
the entire day admitting that...

05:09.309 --> 05:10.219
Gail's awesome.

05:10.268 --> 05:11.724
Yes. (laughs)

05:11.770 --> 05:13.556
So you two actually
had fun together?

05:13.605 --> 05:15.266
(Frank) All right. Listen up.

05:15.315 --> 05:19.649
Another garage fire last night,
north edge of 15 Division.

05:19.694 --> 05:20.945
Detective.

05:20.987 --> 05:23.569
That's four this month,
two in the last week.

05:23.615 --> 05:24.604
(Frank) So keep an eye open.

05:24.658 --> 05:25.898
If there's one thing we know
about firebugs,

05:25.951 --> 05:28.863
it's that they love
to watch their target burn.

05:28.912 --> 05:31.073
(lowered voice) Kind of like me
watching you burn last night.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.446
What a rush.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.036
— (Frank) Peck!
— Oh, yeah.

05:35.085 --> 05:37.246
— Care to share?
— No, we're good.

05:37.295 --> 05:40.378
(clicking)

05:42.634 --> 05:44.590
Detective Barber.

05:44.636 --> 05:46.092
Officer Nash.

05:46.137 --> 05:47.513
What are you doing?

05:47.639 --> 05:50.722
Well, Oliver keeps
coming up behind me,

05:50.934 --> 05:52.595
grabbing my gun out of my holster,
and saying...

05:52.644 --> 05:55.602
"What if I was a suspect?
You'd be dead by now."

05:55.647 --> 05:59.139
So I'm just trying to practice
somebody stealing my gun.

05:59.192 --> 06:00.853
Let me see your interview stance.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.738
Yeah. There's your problem.

06:11.788 --> 06:14.325
Drop your elbows.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.831
You gotta tuck 'em in.

06:16.877 --> 06:19.289
Okay.

06:19.337 --> 06:23.455
You got to feel your gun
at all times.

06:23.508 --> 06:25.544
What are you doing later?

06:25.594 --> 06:28.051
Why? You gonna text me for a hookup?

06:28.096 --> 06:30.212
— Already have.
— Really?

06:30.265 --> 06:33.632
— Mm—hmm.
— Couple of "LOLs," a few "OMGs"?

06:33.685 --> 06:36.677
— Little bit.
— Where the hell's my phone?

06:36.855 --> 06:38.686
Hey, Nash. Hot call.
And by "hot,"

06:38.732 --> 06:40.814
I mean there's a laundromat
on fire at Aldermere Mall.

06:40.859 --> 06:41.689
Arson?

06:41.735 --> 06:44.522
I don't know, do I?
Because I'm not a mentalist.

06:44.571 --> 06:46.778
Let's go.

06:49.784 --> 06:52.821
(click release)
Aw!

06:52.913 --> 06:55.825
(Noelle) Start with the other store owners.
We need statements.

06:55.957 --> 06:56.787
If this is our guy,

06:56.833 --> 06:58.494
good chance he's somewhere
around here, watching.

06:58.543 --> 07:00.750
The place is self—serve,
so it was empty at the time.

07:00.795 --> 07:01.625
That's the good news.

07:01.671 --> 07:05.004
Uh, we're gonna track down the owner
with the alarm company.

07:05.050 --> 07:06.756
In the meantime, we need names.

07:06.801 --> 07:09.668
Find out who saw what,
and report back...

07:11.139 --> 07:13.004
Burnt my pants.

07:14.476 --> 07:15.841
Yeah.

07:16.061 --> 07:17.221
Peck.

07:17.312 --> 07:21.726
Uh, I would talk to him,
but, um, you know, since l——

07:21.775 --> 07:22.605
What is the word?

07:22.692 --> 07:26.605
——humiliated Officer Epstein
in Deathdomain last night...

07:26.655 --> 07:29.488
I can respect that.
Epstein, all yours.

07:29.532 --> 07:32.023
Peck, you're awesome.

07:32.118 --> 07:35.360
(Dov) Excuse me, sir?
Uh, can I talk to you for a second?

07:35.413 --> 07:37.904
You can't go in there yet.
It's very unstable, so...

07:37.958 --> 07:40.745
— (Oliver) What a mess.
— (Andy) What?

07:40.794 --> 07:42.785
Kind of wish
it had burned to the ground.

07:42.837 --> 07:44.293
Why? Easier investigation?

07:44.339 --> 07:48.173
No, we just wouldn't have to spend
all day with the hose monkeys.

07:48.259 --> 07:49.999
Hmm?

07:50.053 --> 07:52.294
One guy's insecure enough——
other guys——

07:52.347 --> 07:55.555
without having to watch
last year's charity calendar

07:55.600 --> 07:57.556
work it out for the ladies.

07:57.602 --> 08:01.470
Shaw, come on. Every girl knows
it's what's inside that counts.

08:01.523 --> 08:04.356
— Man, that's feeble, McNally.
— (chuckles)

08:04.401 --> 08:07.063
Weak. For that you get
guard duty on the door.

08:07.112 --> 08:08.477
— Seriously?
— What?

08:08.530 --> 08:09.519
Okay.

08:11.574 --> 08:15.283
(inhales and exhales deeply)

08:15.328 --> 08:17.705
(breathes deeply)

08:17.747 --> 08:19.362
This is pretty cool, huh?

08:19.416 --> 08:22.499
Looks like the same guy.
Looks like we might have a shot.

08:22.544 --> 08:24.500
All right.
I don't love fire, okay?

08:24.587 --> 08:27.579
Nobody likes fire, Noelle——

08:27.632 --> 08:28.917
No. I'm serious.

08:28.967 --> 08:31.709
I spent my entire childhood
worrying about fire.

08:31.761 --> 08:35.629
Are——Are we gonna go out
this window? That window?

08:35.682 --> 08:37.047
Climb down that tree?

08:37.100 --> 08:40.763
I kept bugging my mom,
you know? I...

08:40.812 --> 08:42.928
I had at least eight exit strategies.

08:43.481 --> 08:44.561
And what'd your mom say?

08:44.607 --> 08:47.019
She gave me a plan, a little map.

08:47.068 --> 08:49.275
Plan A, plan B, plan C.

08:49.320 --> 08:51.697
That's pretty good strategy.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.856
Yeah, she was a pretty good mom.

08:58.246 --> 09:01.204
Yeah, the place was already in flames
when l smelled the smoke,

09:01.249 --> 09:03.240
so I called 911 right away.

09:03.293 --> 09:05.705
Yeah. Uh, do you know the person
who owns the building?

09:05.754 --> 09:07.039
I've seen him around.

09:07.088 --> 09:09.124
Don't know his name, though. Sorry.

09:09.174 --> 09:10.539
Wish I could help you out more.

09:10.592 --> 09:12.207
(Dov) All right, let's go.
Come on.

09:12.260 --> 09:16.173
I had a whole cycle to wait,
felt like a latte. I got back,

09:16.222 --> 09:18.804
the place was locked up.
Kept looking around,

09:18.850 --> 09:22.058
trying to figure out how to get in
and get my pants, when, "boom!"

09:22.103 --> 09:24.845
(Dov) Yeah?
Anybody else watching?

09:26.191 --> 09:27.647
That girl there.

09:32.197 --> 09:35.155
Excuse me. You mind if I ask you
a few questions about the fire?

09:35.200 --> 09:36.656
Uh, can't. I got to go. I'm sorry.

09:36.701 --> 09:39.408
It's not gonna take long.
I just need your name.

09:39.454 --> 09:42.742
Hey, I'm actually not asking you——
Hey! Hey!

09:47.420 --> 09:49.536
You are so busted.

09:58.181 --> 10:00.012
